The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Fans frown at fairer Ash
                                                                                                                                 2                                                                                      Fans frown at fairer Ash
                            
	London, Dec. 24: Elle magazine has been accused of whitening the skin of Aishwarya Rai, who appears on the cover of the magazines Indian edition this month.         
	Readers have accused the publication of digitally bleaching the 37-year-olds skin so that she appears several shades lighter.        
	Inside the magazine, Aishwarya appears in a series of glamorous photographs with pale skin, the Daily Mail has reported.        
	Fans commenting on the cover were upset by the image.        
	One wrote: It seems like lighter skin is always in fashion, as if darker skin is something to be frowned upon.        
	Another said, They photoshop and airbrush ever freaking cover... every magazine does it.        
	The fashion magazine has also been accused of lightening the skin of Precious star Gabourey Sidibe on the cover of its US edition.         
	The magazine, though, has denied it.        
	Skin colour is a sensitive issue in India, where the whitening cream market is worth millions despite opposition from groups who believe the grooming products are discriminatory and outdated.                    THE DAILY TELEGRAPH                                                                                                                                                  
